  "body": "There's potential for a new helper function, which doesn't add much complexity, that could improve efficiency in a few spots, like here. Something like the following method might be a useful addition. Rather than BRP the list of roots, you can just compute the index/indices that you need.\r\n\r\n```python\r\ndef reverse_bits_limited(num_bits: int, value: int):\r\n    reversed_bits = 0\r\n    for _ in range(32): # 32-bit value\r\n        reversed_bits = (reversed_bits << 1) | (value & 1)\r\n        value >>= 1\r\n    unused_bit_len = 32 - int(math.log2(num_bits))\r\n    return reversed_bits >> unused_bit_len\r\n```\r\n\r\n_Originally posted by @jtraglia in https://github.com/ethereum/consensus-specs/pull/3557#discussion_r1416551306_\r\n            ",
